        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kouts, or 9 miles south of Valparaiso, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knox, North Judson, Wanatah, Hamlet, La Crosse, Koontz Lake, Oak
Grove, Hanna, Thomaston, Lomax, Ober, English Lake, South Wanatah,
Brems, Toto, Winona, Bass Lake, and Grovertown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
